title.narrative: SHOPS-Private Sector Health Program- (PSHP) Follow on

description.narrative: (Ethiopia): The Strengthening Health Outcomes though the Private Sector (SHOPS)-PHSP follow-on activity provides technical assistance to 342 private facilities to provide high impact primary health services in private clinics. TB and Malaria funds expand and enhance DOTS and Malaria treatment; MCH/FP/RH and funds will be used to ensure better access and quality of maternal and child health and FP/RH services. With FY 14 fund, the activity will continue providing TA and building the capacity of accredited private clinics to provide quality health care services. The activity will also ensure the flow of TB, malaria and FP commodities and supporting materials from Regional Health Bureaus to private facilities to improve health services. This is in alignment with the Mission's DO2 -increased utilization of quality health services and IR2-Improved health systems. These activities complement those supported by PEPFAR, which support the delivery of HIV services in the private sector.
